{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17643999","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17643999"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:00:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:00:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18030"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18030","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18030"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10744"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73323"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10744","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10744"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18030"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58794"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7310"},{"type":"tags","id":"7405"},{"type":"tags","id":"7406"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25069"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25072"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73323","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73323"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following does not form the boundary of the roof of the neck?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["First rib","Manubrium","Clavicle","T1 vertebra","T2 vertebra"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe roof of the neck is defined by the first rib, the manubrium, and the T1 vertebra. These structures form the superior boundary of the thoracic inlet, which separates the neck from the thoracic cavity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ET2 vertebra\u003C/strong\u003E is not part of the boundary of the roof of the neck. It is located below the T1 vertebra and is part of the thoracic spine, not the boundary of the neck.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFirst rib\u003C/strong\u003E forms the lateral boundary of the roof of the neck.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EManubrium\u003C/strong\u003E forms the anterior boundary of the roof of the neck.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EClavicle\u003C/strong\u003E is not a boundary of the roof of the neck but is located anteriorly and superiorly to the thoracic inlet.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ET1 vertebra\u003C/strong\u003E forms the posterior boundary of the roof of the neck.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The roof of the neck is anatomically defined by specific structures including the first rib, the manubrium, and the thoracic vertebrae.","The second thoracic vertebra (T2) is not part of the boundary of the roof of the neck."],"references":["Fehrenbach, M. J., \u0026 Herring, S. W. (2015). Illustrated Anatomy of the Head and Neck-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, et al. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK534836/","Cramer, G. D., \u0026 Darby, S. A. (2013). Clinical anatomy of the spine, spinal cord, and ANS","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58794"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18030"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia